# Forensic Science Portfolio

## About Me

I am a BSc Medical Biochemistry student at Royal Holloway, University of London with an academic interest in forensic laboratory science, particularly forensic toxicology, pathology, molecular diagnostics, and biological evidence interpretation.

My dissertation project investigated the influence of gold nanoparticles on the sensitivity of LAMP-based assays for viral pathogen detection, strengthening my interest in analytical sensitivity, molecular detection systems, and evidence-based scientific investigation.

This portfolio contains independent projects exploring forensic science concepts, molecular diagnostics, toxicology, pathology, and introductory forensic data analysis.

---

## Portfolio Projects

### 1. LAMP Assays and Molecular Detection
Exploring loop-mediated isothermal amplification (LAMP), assay sensitivity, and applications of molecular diagnostics to forensic and biological detection.

### 2. Forensic Toxicology
A review of toxicological evidence interpretation, detection windows, and biological sample analysis in forensic investigations.

### 3. Forensic Pathology
An overview of post-mortem biological changes and the scientific challenges involved in estimating time since death.

### 4. Forensic Data Analysis in R
Introductory forensic-style data analysis using R, including data visualisation and interpretation.

